# homing — environment variables
#
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values:
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# Most homing workflows require NO environment variables at all.
# The tool runs as a Claude Code subagent and inherits the session's
# authentication — no ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is needed in that mode.
#
# The standalone (non-orchestrator) classify/draft/validate commands
# call the Anthropic API directly and require the key below.

# === Optional: only needed for standalone (non-Claude Code) API calls ===
# When running inside a Claude Code session (the recommended path),
# leave this unset — the session's auth is used automatically.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your-anthropic-api-key-here

# === Advanced: override cabinet's content-class taxonomy ===
# Defaults to the bundled config/content_classes.yaml. Set this only if you
# want to ship a custom taxonomy (e.g. add domain-specific classes like
# "tax-receipts" or "client-deliverables") without forking the repo.
# CABINET_TAXONOMY_PATH=/path/to/your/content_classes.yaml
